IMPORTANT — SCOPE, COMPLIANCE, AND RESPONSIBILITY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This software is an OPEN-SOURCE LIBRARY that generates, validates, and
(deterministically) signs electronic invoices on the customer's own
infrastructure. It is NOT a hosted clearance service and is NOT a certified
e-invoicing platform.

This is NOT tax advice and NOT a compliance guarantee. The library reports
validation results against published rule sets; it does not certify that any
document is legally compliant. Final tax compliance, the integration of a
certified solution, and lawful operation remain the responsibility of the
customer and their professional advisers.

- Saudi Arabia (ZATCA / Fatoora): Live clearance and reporting require an
  onboarded EGS with a ZATCA-issued Production CSID. This library prepares and
  signs documents; clearance/reporting submission must go through the customer's
  own onboarded credentials or a certified partner. Invoice data (which may
  contain personal data) is stored on the customer side; this library does not
  retain it.
- UAE (PINT AE / Peppol), France (PDP), and other jurisdictions: transmission
  via Peppol/PDP requires an Accredited Service Provider / certified platform.
  This library produces and validates documents only; accreditation and
  transmission are delegated to certified partners.

Data residency, retention, and lawful processing obligations are the customer's
responsibility.

